openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  title: Official Anaplan Collection
  version: 1.0.0
  description: >-
    **Welcome to the Anaplan Integration v2 Official Postman Collection**


    **Organization**


    > This collection is organized into  

    > logical groupings of requests. There are several common sequences of
    requests to achieve an outcome in Anaplan. The folders ending in "Flow"
    contain redundant requests organized sequentially.


    **Variables**


    > Collection level variables. These are set at the  

    > collection level and are available within each request. These include
    elements  

    > such as base URLs, model Id and workspace Id. Be sure to click "Save" when
    changing collection level variables.


    > Request specific variables. For variables  

    > specific to a request, we have provided an array in the pre-request script
    area  

    > for you to enter in request specific variables. These will be set prior to
    the  

    > request running.


    **Authentication**


    > There are three methods provided to  

    > authenticate into Anaplan. Once authenticated a Tests script sets the
    value of  

    > the generated token to a variable named “anaplan_auth_token”. You may
    choose to  

    > enter in username/password combination or conversely choose to generate
    CA  

    > certificate signed string and public key combination.
servers:
  - url: https://auth.anaplan.com
  - url: https://us1a.app.anaplan.com
  - url: https://api.anaplan.com
paths:
  /token/authenticate:
    post:
      summary: Create an Authentication Token (Basic)
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          description: Contains the encoded credentials from the Pre-request Script
          schema:
            type: string
          example: Basic {{encodedCredentials}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Authentication
        - Basic Credentials
      security:
        - BasicAuth: []
      description: >-
        [https://anaplanauthentication.docs.apiary.io/#](https://anaplanauthentication.docs.apiary.io/#)


        ## Create an Authentication Token


        `/token/authenticate`  

        To use the version 2.0 API, you must use an Anaplan authentication token
        generated from the Anaplan Authentication Service. You can get an
        authentication token generated using a certificate from a recognized
        external public certificate authority (CA) or using your login and
        password.


        ### Create an authentication token using a username & password


        Creates an AnaplanAuthToken.


        Use your Anaplan username and password to generate an authentication
        token. You can use this authentication token in your API requests.


        **Note**: If your workspace uses single sign-on (SSO), your user must be
        assigned as an Exception User to use basic authentication and obtain an
        Anaplan authentication token. For more information on exception users in
        Anaplan, see [Assign Exception
        Users](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Administration_and_Security/Security/Single_Sign-on/Enforcing_SAML_Authentication.html)
        in Anapedia.
  /oauth/token:
    post:
      summary: Obtain Refresh Token
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Authentication
        - OAuth2
  /token/refresh:
    post:
      summary: Refresh Authentication Token
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          description: >-
            This contains the auth token generated in a prior authentication
            request
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Authentication
        - Other Authentication Actions
      description: "## Refresh authentication token\n\n`/token/refresh`  \n\nGenerates a new authentication token from an existing\_`{anaplan_auth_token}`\_that you provide. You need to refresh your token if your session runs for longer than 30 minutes."
  /token/validate:
    get:
      summary: Get Authentication Token Details
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Authentication
        - Other Authentication Actions
      description: "## Get authentication token details\n\n`/token/validate`  \n\nGets information on a provided\_`{anaplan_auth_token}`. If the token is valid, returns the details of the\_`{anaplan_auth_token}`. If the token is invalid, returns a \"401 UnAuthorized\" message."
  /token/logout:
    post:
      summary: Log Out the User
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Authentication
        - Other Authentication Actions
      description: "## Log out the user\n\n`/token/logout`  \n\nDeletes an\_`{anaplan_auth_token}`. After the /logout command, the\_`{anaplan_auth_token}`\_is deleted and no longer valid.\n\nNo response body is expected. If response code is 204 then user has been logged out successfully."
  /2/0/users/me:
    get:
      summary: Retrieve your user
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          required: false
          deprecated: false
          schema: {}
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - User Data
      description: "## Retrieve your user\n\n`/users/me`  \n\nRetrieves your user based on your Anaplan authentication token.\n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET \\\nhttps://api.anaplan.com/2/0/users/me \\\n-H 'authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}' \\\n-H \"Content-Type:application/json\"\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n| **Header** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: the Anaplan authentication token<br><br> |\n| `Accept: application/json` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: This indicates the preferred response is either\_`application/json`\_format. Note that this call only outputs in\_`application/json`\_format.<br><br> |"
  /2/0/users/{userId}:
    get:
      summary: Retrieve user information
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - User Data
      description: "## Retrieve user information\n\n`/users/{userId}`  \nRetrieves information about the specified user.\n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET \\\nhttps://api.anaplan.com/2/0/users/{userId} \\\n-H 'authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}' \\\n-H \"Content-Type:application/json\"\n```\n\n### Headers\n\n*   `Authorization:AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}`\n*   `Content-Type:application/json`\n    \n\n### Parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `userId` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: string<br>*   Description: The user ID<br>*   Example:\_`8a8196a55b193fa0015b1e57f3da172c`<br><br> |"
    parameters:
      - name: userId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: '{{userId}}'
  /2/0/models:
    get:
      summary: List user models
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - General Workspace & Model Metadata
      description: "## Retrieve models\n\n`/models`  \nRetrieves information about all models in the user's default tenant.\n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET \\\nhttps://api.anaplan.com/2/0/models \\\n-H 'authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}'\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n`Authorization:AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}`\n\n### Request parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{modelDetails}` | <br><br>*   Optional<br>*   Type: Boolean<br>*   Description: When set to\_`true`, this call returns the available model memory usage in bytes. When set to\_`false`, or not defined, this call does not return the model memory usage.<br>*   Example:\_`?modelDetails=true`<br><br> |\n\n### Response 200 (application/json)\n\n```\n{\n\_ \"meta\": {\n\_\_\_ \"schema\": \"https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/objects/model\",\n\_\_\_ \"paging\": {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"currentPageSize\": 1,\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"totalSize\": 1,\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"offset\": 0\n\_\_\_ }\n\_ },\n\_ \"status\": {\n\_\_\_ \"code\": 200,\n\_\_\_ \"message\": \"Success\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"models\": [{\n\_\_\_\_\_ id\": \"FC12345678912343455667\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"activeState\": \"UNLOCKED\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\": \"FP&A\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"currentWorkspaceId\": \"8a8b8c8d8e8f8g8i\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"currentWorkspaceName\": \"Financial Planning\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"modelUrl\": \"https://rt.anaplan.com/anaplan/rt?selectedWorkspaceId\\8a8b8c8d8e8f8g8i\\u0026selectedModelId\\FC12345678912343455667\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"categoryValues\": []\n\_\_\_}]\n}\n```"
  /2/0/workspaces:
    get:
      summary: List user workspaces
      parameters:
        - name: tenantDetails
          in: query
          schema:
            type: boolean
          example: true
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - General Workspace & Model Metadata
      description: "## List user workspaces\n\n`/workspaces`  \n\nRetrieves all workspaces a user has access to within the user's default tenant\n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET \\\nhttps://api.anaplan.com/2/0/workspaces?tenantDetails=true \\\n-H 'authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}'\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n| **Header** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: the Anaplan authentication token<br><br> |\n\n### Request parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `tenantDetails` | <br><br>*   Optional<br>*   Type: Boolean<br>*   Description: When set to true, this call returns an estimate of the current size of the workspace from all the models it contains. When set to false, or not defined, this call does not return an estimated current size of the workspace.<br>*   Example: true<br><br> |\n\n### Response headers\n\n`Content-Type: application/json`\n\n### Response 200 body\n\n```\n{\n\_ \"meta\": {\n\_\_\_ \"schema\": \"https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/objects/workspace\",\n\_\_\_ \"paging\": {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"currentPageSize\": 1,\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"totalSize\": 1,\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"offset\": 0\n\_\_\_ }\n\_ },\n\_ \"status\": {\n\_\_\_ \"code\": 200,\n\_\_\_ \"message\": \"Success\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"workspaces\": [\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_ \"id\": \"8a8b8c8d8e8f8g8i\",\n\_\_\_ \"name\": \"Financial Planning\",\n\_\_\_ \"active\": true,\n\_\_\_ \"sizeAllowance\": 1073741824,\n\_\_\_ \"currentSize\": 873741824\n\_\_\_ }\n\_ ]\n}\n\n```"
  /2/0/workspaces/{workspaceId}:
    get:
      summary: Get single workspace metadata
      parameters:
        - name: tenantDetails
          in: query
          schema:
            type: boolean
          example: true
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - General Workspace & Model Metadata
    parameters:
      - name: workspaceId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: 8a868cda7c8b28f5017c9a4b2d8341cd
  /2/0/models/{modelId}:
    get:
      summary: Get single model metadata
      parameters:
        - name: modelDetails
          in: query
          schema:
            type: boolean
          example: true
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - General Workspace & Model Metadata
    parameters:
      - name: modelId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: 4261ECE4389B45E18915B5EB72F7510B
  /2/0/workspaces/{workspaceId}/models/{modelId}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items:
    post:
      summary: Lookup dimension items by name or code
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Model Metadata
        - List Metadata
      description: "## Lookup dimension items by name or code\n\nRetrieve the items from a dimension that match one of a list of names or a list or codes.\n\n** Notes: **\n\n*   To use this call, you must be a\_[Workspace Administrator](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Administration_and_Security/Workspace_Administration.html).\n*   This call does not return results for names or codes for which an item does not exist.\n*   If the given workspace, model, or dimension do not exist, this call returns a\_`404`\_code.\n*   If the dimension does not support codes and codes are provided, this call returns a\_`400`\_code.\n*   In the future, use of this call may be rate limited.\n    \n\n### Requests that support this feature\n\n```\ncurl -X POST https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/workspaces/{workspaceId}/models/{modelId}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items \\\n-H ‘Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}' \\\n-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n-H 'Accept: application/json' --data-raw ''\n\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n| **Header** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: the Anaplan authentication token<br><br> |\n| `Content-Type: application/json` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: This indicates the request format is\_`application/json`.<br><br> |\n| `Accept: application/json` | <br><br>*   Optional<br>*   Description: This indicates the preferred response is either\_`application/json`\_format. Note that this call only outputs in\_`application/json`\_format.<br><br> |\n\n### Request parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{workspaceId}` | <br><br>*   Required in the supported request<br>*   Type: String<br>*   Description: The workspace ID<br>*   Example:\_`8a8196b15b7dbae6015b8694411d13fe`<br><br> |\n| `{modelId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: String<br>*   Description: the model ID<br>*   Example:\_`75A40874E6B64FA3AE074327899685`<br><br> |\n| `{dimensionId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: Number<br>*   Description: the dimension ID. This value must be the ID for any of these dimension types:<br>    *   Lists<br>    *   Time periods<br>    *   Users<br>    *   Versions<br>*   Example:\_`101000000001`<br><br> |\n\n### Request body\n\n| **JSON Element** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `names` | The case-insensitive strings that match the name of a returned item. |\n| `codes` | The case-insensitive strings that match the code of a returned item. |\n\nExample:\n\n```\n{\n    \"names\": [\"South\", \"East\"],\n    \"codes\": [\"N\", \"W\"]\n}\n\n```\n\nNote that the\_`names`,\_`codes`, or both fields in the request body must contain a non-empty value. If the request body does not include at least one of these fields, the response returns an error.\n\n### Response 200 Body\n\n```\n{\n  \"meta\" : {\n      \"schema\":\"https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/objects/dimension\"\n  },\n  \"status\" : {\n    \"code\":200,\n    \"message\":\"Success\"\n  },\n  \"items\":[\n    {\n      \"name\":\"South\",\n      \"id\":\"208000000001\",\n      \"code\":\"S\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\":\"West\",\n      \"id\":\"208000000004\",\n      \"code\":\"W\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              type: object
              properties:
                codes:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
                    format: utc-millisec
                names:
                  type: array
                  items:
                    type: string
            example:
              codes:
                - '2'
              names:
                - Test1
    parameters:
      - name: workspaceId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: 8a868cda7c8b28f5017c9a4b2d8341cd
      - name: modelId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: 4261ECE4389B45E18915B5EB72F7510B
      - name: dimensionId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: '{{dimensionId}}'
    get:
      summary: Retrieve all items in a dimension
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Model Metadata
        - List Metadata
      description: "## Retrieve all items in a dimension\n\n`/models/{modelGuid}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items`\n\nUse this call to retrieve the IDs, codes, and names for items in a specified dimension. The dimension must be a list, a list subset, a line item subset, or the Users dimension.\n\nCalls at model-level do not support the Time dimension. The calls return a\_`400`\_response. To avoid this, use the view dimension instead.\n\n**Notes**:\n\n*   To use this call, you must be a\_[Workspace Administrator](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Administration_and_Security/Workspace_Administration.html).\n*   This call is on the model-level. It returns all dimension items as it does not have view-level hiding, filtering, or\_[Selective Access](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Modeling/Users/Selective_Access.html). For the view-level endpoint, see\_[Retrieve selected items in a dimension](https://anaplanbulkapi20.docs.apiary.io/#RetrieveSelectedItemsDimension).\n*   If codes have not been set for an item, then the response excludes the\_`code`\_field.\n*   This call only supports the retrieval of dimensions and items from a dimension that contains a maximum of 1,000,000 items.  \n    The call returns a\_`400`\_response for any more than that number of items.\n*   Use of this call may be rate limited. If you call too frequently, you may receive a\_`429`\_response.\n    \n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET\n'https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/models/{modelGuid}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items'\\\n-H 'Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}'\\\n-H 'Accept: application/json'\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n| **Header** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: the Anaplan authentication token<br><br> |\n| `Accept: application/json` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: This indicates the preferred response is\_`application/json`\_format.<br><br> |\n\n### Request parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{modelId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: String<br>*   Description: the ID for the model<br>*   Example:\_`75A40874E6B64FA3AE074327899685`<br><br> |\n| `{dimensionId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: Number<br>*   Description: the ID for the dimension<br>*   Example:\_`101000000028`<br><br> |\n\n### Response headers\n\n`Content-Type: application/json`\n\n### Response 200 Body\n\n```\n{\n\_ \"meta\" : {\n\_\_\_ \"schema\" : \"https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/objects/dimension\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"status\" : {\n\_\_\_ \"code\" : 200,\n\_\_\_ \"message\" : \"Success\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"items\" : [\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"code\" : \"N\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\" : \"200000000001\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\" : \"North\"\n\_\_\_ },\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"code\" : \"E\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\" : \"200000000002\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\" : \"East\"\n\_\_\_ },\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"code\" : \"S\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\" : \"200000000003\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\" : \"South\"\n\_\_\_ },\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"code\" : \"W\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\" : \"200000000004\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\" : \"West\"\n\_\_\_ },\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\" : \"200000000000\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\" : \"Total Company\"\n\_\_\_ }\n\_ ]\n}\n```"
  /2/0/models/{modelId}/views/{viewId}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items:
    get:
      summary: Retrieve selected items in a dimension
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
        - Model Metadata
        - List Metadata
      description: "## Retrieve selected items in a dimension\n\n`/models/{modelId}/views/{viewId}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items`\n\nUse this call to retrieve selected IDs, codes, and names for items in a specified dimension. This call returns data as filtered by the page builder when they configure the view. This call respects hidden items, filtering selections, and\_[Selective Access](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Modeling/Users/Selective_Access.html). If the view contains hidden or filtered items, these do not display in the response.\n\n**Notes**:\n\n*   To use this call, you must be a\_[Workspace Administrator](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Administration_and_Security/Workspace_Administration.html)\n*   This call works with any dimension type\n*   The items in the response may not be ordered\n*   The response returns Items within a\_[flat list](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/Modeling/Dimensions/Lists.html)\_(no hierarchy)\n*   This is a view-level call. For the model-level call, see\_[Retrieve all data for items in a dimension](https://anaplanbulkapi20.docs.apiary.io/#RetrieveItemsDimension)\n*   This call only supports the retrieval of dimension items within a view that contains a maximum of 1,000,000 cells. If the specified view contains more than 1,000,000 dimension items, then the call returns a\_`400 Bad Request`\_HTTP status, instead of a subset of the dimension items. Use the\_[quick sum bar](https://help.anaplan.com/anapedia/Content/New_User_Experience/Use/Worksheets/Grid/Quick-sum-bar.htm)\_in Anaplan to identify the number of dimension items in a view\n*   Use of this call may be rate limited. If you call too frequently, you may receive a\_`429`\_response\n*   The\_`viewId`\_in this request can also be replaced by any valid\_`lineItemId`. If the Line Item has a changed dimensionality (has a Subsidiary View), the response returns the applicable dimension items for the given dimension. Otherwise, the response returns all default applicable dimension items for the given dimension\n    \n\n### Request\n\n```\ncurl -X GET 'https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/models/{modelId}/views/{viewId}/dimensions/{dimensionId}/items' \\\n-H 'Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}' \\\n-H 'Accept: application/json'\n```\n\n### Request headers\n\n| **Header** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `Authorization: AnaplanAuthToken {anaplan_auth_token}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: the Anaplan authentication token<br><br> |\n| `Accept: application/json` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Description: This indicates the preferred response is\_`application/json`\_format.<br><br> |\n\n### Request parameters\n\n| **Parameter** | **Details** |\n| --- | --- |\n| `{modelId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: String<br>*   Description: the ID for the model<br>*   Example:\_`75A40874E6B64FA3AE074327899685`<br><br> |\n| `{viewId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: Number<br>*   Description: the ID for the view<br>*   Example:\_`102000000000`<br><br> |\n| `{dimensionId}` | <br><br>*   Required<br>*   Type: Number<br>*   Description: the ID for the dimension<br>*   Example:\_`101000000028`<br><br> |\n\n### Response header\n\n`Content-Type: application/json`\n\n### Response 200 Body\n\n```\n{\n\_ \"meta\": {\n\_\_\_ \"schema\": \"https://api.anaplan.com/2/0/objects/dimension\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"status\": {\n\_\_\_ \"code\": 200,\n\_\_\_ \"message\": \"Success\"\n\_ },\n\_ \"items\": [{\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\": \"220000000001\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\": \"England\"\n\_\_\_ },\n\_\_\_ {\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"id\": \"220000000002\",\n\_\_\_\_\_ \"name\": \"Wales\"\n    }]\n}\n\n```"
    parameters:
      - name: modelId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: 4261ECE4389B45E18915B5EB72F7510B
      - name: viewId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: ''
      - name: dimensionId
        in: path
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
        example: '{{dimensionId}}'
  /2/0/workspaces/{workspaceId}/models/{modelId}/lists:
    get:
      summary: Retrieve Lists
      parameters:
        - name: Authorization
          in: header
          schema:
            type: string
          example: AnaplanAuthToken {{anaplan_auth_token}}
      responses: {}
      tags:
